Wonderful production and dining spoiled by poor theatre etiquette.
Nov 2024 â€¢ Couples
Alex and the musicians were excellent! The food was great! The set up was superb!

However, there were two disappointing elements with theatre etiquette a real issue. See later.

Firstly, whilst the food was great, on both the starter and main courses we had side dishes missing and had to request these spoiling the experience. Disappointing and frustrating.

I really wanted to give this review five stars but the wonderful performance was spoiled by dreadful theatre etiquette of many watching.

I had to request people nearby to stop using their phones (not for photos which are allowed without flash, but in sending texts or generally scrolling!). Doing this with your phone under the table does not hide the glaring light; especially when much of the production is in dim atmospheric lighting! It was not an isolated incident with a number of people seemingly unable to live without their phones for a couple of hours! Really?!!! Also, I had to politely ask people behind us from talking incessantly (and loudly) throughout the early stages of the second session! It is my firm belief (having made enquiries) that there were a number of staff from The Lost Estate either enjoying a free or reduced rate viewing. If so, then clearly some were not as invested in the performance (either attentivelyâ€¦â€¦and perhaps financially) as those of us that were true paying attendees. It may indeed have been a preview night but we paid the best part of Â£500 for the evening for two, only to be frustrated by disrespectful individuals with no regard for those of us there wanting to be fully immersed in this wonderful production. We may have received a Â£50 discount per ticket for a preview show, but that does not mean the experience should be in anyway less than expected.

A recommendation would also be for a brief announcement to be made alerting people to the restart of the performance after each course. A number of people were prohibited from returning to their seats for some time having visited the toilet. Quite right given the set up and so as not to disturb others, but no warning was given which would have avoided this happening.
